{"version":"0.2","metadata":{"infracostCommand":"breakdown","vcsBranch":"main","vcsCommitSha":"2bd9f4f54d815e515d02de70720a94258c7c5518","vcsCommitAuthorName":"taichenjie","vcsCommitAuthorEmail":"chenjie470@gmail.com","vcsCommitTimestamp":"2026-06-18T16:03:50Z","vcsCommitMessage":"feat: complete Q1 M1 network — VPC endpoints, IAM boundary, SSM access\n\n- S3 gateway endpoint (free, route added to private RT)\n- Endpoint security group (HTTPS 443 from VPC CIDR, no egress)\n- SSM family interface endpoints in private-az1 only:\n  ssm, ssmmessages, ec2messages — all required for SSM Session Manager\n- ECR interface endpoints in private-az1 only:\n  ecr.api, ecr.dkr — both required for image push/pull\n  S3 gateway endpoint covers ECR's internal S3 layer storage traffic\n- Single-AZ endpoint placement documented in ADR-002\n  (cost vs HA trade-off, matches NAT's single-AZ design)\n\n- IAM permission boundary policy (Allow * + Deny IAM escalation,\n  boundary protection, account/org/KMS destruction). Applies as the\n  ceiling for every non-root principal we create in this environment.\n\n- EC2 SSM access role bounded by the permission boundary, with the\n  AWS-managed AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore policy attached. Wrapped\n  in an instance profile.\n\n- VPC module: new nat_instance_profile_name input variable.\n  NAT instance now carries the SSM instance profile, making it\n  reachable via aws ssm start-session for the first apply's verify step.\n\nPlan: 31 to add, 0 billable resources applied. First apply deferred to\nthe next session to keep apply attention focused, not end-of-day.","vcsRepositoryUrl":"https://github.com/taichenjie/platform10"},"currency":"USD","projects":[{"name":"taichenjie/platform10/infra/terraform/environments/dev/tfplan.json","displayName":"","metadata":{"path":"infra/terraform/environments/dev/tfplan.json","type":"terraform_plan_json","policySha":"b26a86a5a33b35486d2ccbbd8590c455c97f6781","pastPolicySha":"0","vcsSubPath":"infra/terraform/environm